As the Portfolio project already uses the old technologies I did the following

1. To run this project with 'npm start'
 change in 'package.json' the "start": "react-scripts start",
 to "start": "react-scripts --openssl-legacy-provider start". 
 
 2. Install the Firebase and then Firebase tools running the following commands in consode. 
 a. npm i firebase --legacy-peer-deps
 b. npm i firebase-tools --legacy-peer-deps
 
 3. Install the firebase-tools packages on Linux. Put in Terminal
 sudo npm i -g firebase-tools
 
 4. Create a "build" folder of the static files of your project by running:
a. npm rund build
b. If 'a' didn't work, then 'NODE_OPTIONS='--openssl-legacy-provider' npm run build'
 
 5. Enter in the folder root of your project 'firebase init'
 
